The milk and domestic water samples were analyzed separately and no OFL was detected, indicating that the milk and domestic water was acceptable. In order to use the obtained β-CD-N,Zn-CDs for the determination of OFL in the actual sample, pretreatment will be carried out for milk. The pretreatment process has almost no effect on the detection of OFL, and the experiment was carried out by using β-CD-N,Zn-CDs fluorescence intensity to verify. The results are shown in Table 1
                        . The milk samples recovery rates are from 87.5% to 108.5% with RSD from 3.5% to 4.2%, and the domestic water samples recovery rates are from 88.7% to 110.6% with RSD from 3.8% to 4.7%. The comparison of different analytical methods for the determination of OFL (Table 2
                        ). The fluorescence detection method is green and environmental protection, Generation of a large volume of analytical waste be avoided, and is easy to operate, in line with the 12 principles of green analytical chemistry (GAC) [25]. This method without expensive or sophisticated instrumentations, extensive sample preparation, and more skilled person required. The results show that the β-CD-N,Zn-CDs is suitable for the detection of OFL in actual samples.
